\p{After the next reading was the original traditonal arrangement of the [Coventry Carol](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WII-nEAykqY) with the crunchy false relation in the cadence.}
\quote{
  \poem{
    \line{Lully, lullay, þow littell tyne childe,}
    \line{by, by, lully, lullay.}
    \line{þow littell tyne childe:}
    \line{by, by, lully, lullay.}
    \line{\br}
    \line{O! Sisters too, how may we do}
    \line{for to preserve this day}
    \line{this pore yongling for whom we do singe:}
    \line{by, by, lully, lullay?}
    \line{\br}
    \line{Herod, the king, in his raging,}
    \line{chargid he hath this day,}
    \line{his men of might in his owne sight,}
    \line{all yonge children to slay.}
    \line{\br}
    \line{That wo is me, pore childe, for Thee}
    \line{and ever morne and day}
    \line{for thi parting nether say nor singe:}
    \line{by, by, lully, lullay.}
  }
}
\p{The next reading was followed by [O little town of Bethlehem](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LRuXdOb6TrA) with the Willcocks descant. Then, after the next reading we sang the \em{significantly} less common arrangement of the Basque carol \em{Gabriel's Message}, also known as \em{the Angel Gabriel} or the [Most Highly Flavoured Gravy](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RJnJ6Ko_kyw).}
\quote{
  \poem{
    \line{The Angel Gabriel from heaven came,}
    \line{his wings as drifted snow, his eyes as flame;}
    \line{'All hail', said he, 'thou lowly maiden Mary}
    \line{Most highly favoured lady, \em{Gloria}.'}
    \line{\br}
    \line{'For known a blesséd Mother thou shalt be,}
    \line{all generations laud and honour thee,}
    \line{thy Son shall be Immanuel by seers foretold;}
    \line{Most highly favoured lady, \em{Gloria}.'}
    \line{\br}
    \line{Then gentle Mary meekly bowed her head,}
    \line{'To me be as it pleaseth God', she said,}
    \line{'My soul shall laud and magnify his holy name':}
    \line{most highly favoured lady, \em{Gloria}.}
    \line{\br}
    \line{Of her, Immanuel, the Christ was born}
    \line{in Bethlehem all on a Christmas morn,}
    \line{and Christian folk throughout the world will ever say:}
    \line{'most highly favoured lady, \em{Gloria}.'}
  }
}
\p{After one more reading, we performed what I think was a highlight of the whole service, and one of our best performances, Lauridsen's [O Magnum Mysterium](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tZ-nuU-hda8):}
\quote{
